webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) The new church in Hägerstad was erected in 1864-66 after drawings by Carl Gustaf Blom-Carlsson. The architect created a completely through neo-Gothic creation. His original proposal was not entirely implemented, yet the church is an example of the architectural conception of the time - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000554. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419870. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
